msContents.summary: Collection of about 800 poems in Sicilian dialect by Antoni Vinizianu, Cesaru or Zesaru Gravina, Liuni Russelli [=Leone Rosselli?], Micheli Moraschinu, Giuseppi Durazzu, Jacupu Morellu, Gabrieli Ciceru or Cicero, Giuseppi Morettu, Vincenzu Giuffrè [=Gioffre?], Antoni Carvuni [or Carvoni, Carvini?], Giuseppi Galeanu, Andrá Rizzu, Gilormu La M'ana or Lamanna, Petru La Dunzella, Franciscu Gaita, and "di diversi." Names from table of contents (f. ii recto); alphabetical index of beginnings of verses at end of volume. According to the table of contents, numbered f. 137-146 are missing, containing the work Luntananza di Frà Don Cesaru Gravina.

msItem.title: Table of contents, f. ii recto

supportDesc.extent: 315 leaves : 205 x 153 mm. bound to 210 x 159 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 315; [iv], 1-136, 147-254, [lxvii], contemporary foliation in ink, upper right recto; [iv, 1-311]; modern foliation in pencil, lower right recto. Upper and lower pastedown have come loose. References in this record are to the contemporary foliation.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by one hand, with the exception of a few additions, (f. 253r-254r).

decoDesc.decoNote: Illuminated title with foliated design and illuminated initial (f. 1r).

binding.p: Contemporary gilt morocco. Leather from upper and lower edges of spine missing.

origin.p: Written in Sicily in the second half of the 17th century (Zacour-Hirsch).
